# 1. 集うアイドル達

Saito: Thank you all for your patience! I've finished registering us, so let's make our way inside.
Haruka: Thank you for taking care of that, Saito.
Saito: Not a problem! Still, this orientation event is bigger than I was anticipating...
Airi: Same here. I'm seeing a lot of reporters and photographers, not just the idols and staff.
Airi: I guess it means the Lumina Grand Prix is just that big a deal.
Minori: *Gasp* Look, it's...!
Shizuku: Is that Arisa...?
Airi: Huh?
Haruka: I see... The members of ReLight and Cheerful * Days are also here.
Airi: Yeah. That was probably to be expected, but...
???: Good morning, everyone!!!
???: I'm Hikarin, the biggest idol in the galaxy☆ My smile has the power to brighten up the entire universe!
Hikarin: All you reporters out there better get pictures of me now, because I might just end up this competition's dark-horse winner!
Haruka: Is she new? It's nice how peppy she is.
Minori: D-Do you think we should introduce ourselves like that too...?!
Airi: No need for that, so try to calm down.
Airi: (There really are all sorts of different idols here... Some from the underground scene, and plenty of others I'm seeing for the first time. They're all unique, from their personalities to their experience level.)
Airi: (The only thing we all have in common is that we were sent invitations by Ms. Arisawa...)
Minori: So, your true identity is the legendary idol, Hinako Arisawa...
Minori: And you're organizing a program called the Lumina Grand Prix...?!
Airi: (“A program that decides who the best idols are.”)
Airi: (In other words, we'd be competing against other idols to see who's number one.)
Arisawa: I apologize if I startled all of you.
Arisawa: But I'd appreciate it very much if you all attended the orientation session and heard more.
Haruka: Orientation?
Arisawa: Yes. It should give MORE MORE JUMP! a chance to see whether or not this program's goals align with your own.
Arisawa: I'd like for you to have that opportunity before you make a decision.
Airi: (Our goal as a group is to spread more hope than anyone else...)
Airi: (We've been doing everything we can up until now to make that happen.)
Airi: (While that's led to offers trickling back in, there's no denying that we're still in a tough spot...)
Airi: (So, we need to see if this is our opportunity to turn things around.)
Arisawa: Thank you all for being here today.
Arisawa: My name is Hinako Arisawa, and I'm the organizer of this program. I hope this orientation proves fruitful for you all.
Airi: ...!
Minori: Ms. Arisawa...!
Arisawa: At any rate, I'll jump right in by explaining what the Lumina Grand Prix is all about.
Arisawa: The overall concept is “a program that decides who the best idols are.”
Arisawa: I'm sure many of you are here today because you were drawn to that thought.
Arisawa: As a television program, the Lumina Grand Prix is a competition between idols all striving for the top...
Arisawa: But that's all set up for the viewers' entertainment. It is not the true goal of this program.
Airi: (What?)
Arisawa: Before we move to the finer details, I'd like to first discuss why I decided to create this program...
Arisawa: Through this competition...
Arisawa: I'm hoping to bring out the “true idols” in each of you. For everyone in the country... No, for everyone around the world to see.
